 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","title":"[FCP3/P4.1] Refactor fcp-host into a node local root app over lower layer semantics","description":"Background: fcp-host is currently the practical center of the system because it owns too much semantic meaning. In the target architecture it should remain important, but as a node local orchestrator over lower layers rather than as the source of platform truth.

Scope: refactor fcp-host so it consumes kernel, policy, evidence, and durable plane contracts instead of defining them. Supervision, orchestration, and local process management should remain in host, but execution meaning, policy meaning, and evidence meaning should come from the crates that own them. Preserve structured supervision, lifecycle, and evidence logs aligned with the lower layer vocabulary so later integration and end to end beads can compare host behavior across native, WASI, and failover paths without special case interpretation.

Acceptance: host becomes a consumer and coordinator, not the semantic owner of the platform, and host diagnostics align with the canonical lower layer vocabulary instead of reintroducing parallel meanings.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"SageDuck","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:32:06.068633Z","created_by":"CobaltHarbor","updated_at":"2026-04-01T17:50:02.644739Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T17:46:16.977914Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fcp3","fcp3-refoundation","host","mesh-first","phase-4","refactor"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-d8jbq","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:32:29.293485Z","created_by":"CobaltHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-gg5sl","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:32:30.386821Z","created_by":"CobaltHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-ndoro","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:32:31.014754Z","created_by":"CobaltHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-vqfld","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:32:29.848634Z","created_by":"CobaltHarbor","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2095,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"SageDuck","text":"Claimed a narrow execution-control carve under this bead after repo archaeology and coordination with active agents. Current implementation moves CancelReason, CleanupBehavior, ProgressUnit, and ProgressUpdate from fcp-host-local definitions into new fcp-kernel ownership, with fcp-host re-exporting the kernel types to preserve the current host API surface while the broader node-local root app refactor proceeds.","created_at":"2026-03-29T02:20:28Z"},{"id":2097,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"SageDuck","text":"Verification update: remote-only rch checking was attempted and aborted immediately on fail-open before local cargo could proceed. Verbose rch preflight reported a workspace path-cycle blocker rather than a host/kernel code error: resolver produced cyclic path dependency rooted at /Users/jemanuel/projects/flywheel_connectors/crates/fcp-core with reason code RCH-E326. Local manifest archaeology points to a real Cargo path cycle through test-only edges (fcp-core dev-dep -> fcp-testkit -> fcp-conformance -> fcp-core) plus a direct fcp-testkit <-> fcp-conformance test-helper entanglement via LogCapture. My host/kernel carve itself remains fcp-host -> fcp-kernel -> fcp-core, which is acyclic.","created_at":"2026-03-29T02:28:02Z"},{"id":2105,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"jemanuel","text":"Implemented the next narrow tbjdk execution-control ownership carve. Moved host-shared semantic wire types into crates/fcp-kernel: cancellation vocabulary (CancellationOutcome, CancellationRequest, CancellationResponse, PartialResult, CheckpointInfo, CleanupResult, CancellationAuditEvent) plus progress vocabulary (PhaseTransition, ProgressNotification, ProgressPayload, ProgressOptions, AggregatedProgress). Host now re-exports those kernel-owned types from cancellation.rs and progress.rs while keeping CancellationController and ProgressController host-local. Added chrono workspace dependency to fcp-kernel and kernel-side unit coverage for moved defaults/serde stability. Local rustfmt on touched Rust files passed. Remote verification attempt was compliant-only via RCH_VERBOSE=1 rch exec -- cargo check -p fcp-kernel --lib; it selected vmi1156319 and got through topology preflight, but exact dependency closure sync expanded to 188 dirty roots and never reached remote cargo before I interrupted it to avoid a long-running repo-scale sync. No local cargo fallback was allowed to run.","created_at":"2026-03-29T03:18:05Z"},{"id":2106,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"jemanuel","text":"Continued tbjdk with a second semantic-ownership carve. Moved rollout vocabulary into crates/fcp-kernel and left RolloutController plus host-specific rollout gating/runtime logic in crates/fcp-host/src/rollout.rs. Kernel now owns RolloutObservation, RolloutDecision (with public stable as_str labels), RolloutAuditEvent, RolloutEvidence (including digest), and RolloutOutcome; fcp-host re-exports them. Added blake3 workspace dependency to fcp-kernel and kernel-side unit coverage for rollout label stability and evidence digest determinism. Local rustfmt on touched Rust files passed. I did not run a second fresh RCH cargo attempt for this follow-on slice because the immediately prior compliant rch exec on fcp-kernel never reached remote cargo and was still syncing the 188-root exact dirty dependency closure when interrupted.","created_at":"2026-03-29T03:23:16Z"},{"id":2143,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"BronzeCondor","text":"BronzeCondor taking a narrow non-overlapping tbjdk sub-slice after AGENTS/README/code archaeology. Planned change: make fcp-host consume more kernel-owned execution/lifecycle vocabulary through fcp-kernel reexports instead of importing those shared semantics directly from fcp-core, while staying off active store/GC surfaces and without changing host-local supervisor behavior. Agent Mail file reservations are currently unreliable in this repo, so coordination is being mirrored here in beads comments.","created_at":"2026-03-31T03:29:34Z"},{"id":2147,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"BronzeCondor","text":"Completed a narrow host/kernel consumer refactor slice in fcp-host: doctor.rs, discovery.rs, rollout.rs, agent_api.rs, and bin/fcp-host.rs now import more execution/lifecycle semantics (ConnectorId, OperationInfo, Introspection, request/response types, lifecycle/self-check vocabulary, etc.) from fcp-kernel rather than fcp-core, while leaving core-owned policy/security types in place. No intended behavior change; this is an ownership-boundary cleanup aligned with tbjdk. Remote verification attempt was compliant-only via rch exec -- cargo check -p fcp-host --all-targets. rch selected worker vmi1149989 but hit dependency-preflight fail-open RCH-E326 before remote cargo could run, then started a local fallback cargo check which I immediately terminated to stay within repo policy. rch status later showed the failed build as a 550ms remote-preflight failure, and worker capabilities refresh confirmed the fleet has the needed nightly, so current verification remains blocked on rch/dependency-preflight state rather than on a captured Rust compile error. Agent Mail intro/contact attempts still fail in this repo due malformed SQLite pages, so coordination is being mirrored here.","created_at":"2026-03-31T03:36:32Z"},{"id":2150,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"Codex","text":"Read AGENTS.md and README.md fully, then mapped the current fwc/fcp-host/fcp-core/fcp-kernel architecture. Agent Mail remains degraded in this repo for write paths: ensure_project and list_agents succeed, but register_agent still returns 'Resource is temporarily busy', so I cannot yet introduce myself or reserve files there. To keep work moving without colliding with SageDuck/BronzeCondor, I am taking a narrow non-overlapping tbjdk slice in untouched host files: migrate remaining host-side imports of kernel-owned execution/lifecycle/resource-accounting vocabulary from fcp-core to fcp-kernel in admin_state.rs and budget.rs (and only adjacent untouched files if the same ownership cleanup is clearly local). I am explicitly staying off the currently active discovery/doctor/rollout/agent_api/bin/fcp-host surfaces and off store/conformance files already modified in the worktree.","created_at":"2026-03-31T03:50:22Z"},{"id":2153,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-tbjdk","author":"Codex","text":"Progress update on the narrow tbjdk ownership-cleanup slic