 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-the4k","title":"TEST-CONFORMANCE-2: session MAC suite-binding + session_id-binding cross-input independence","description":"datagram_golden_vectors covers MAC direction-binding, seq-binding, wrong-key, and byte-tamper. Missing: (1) suite-binding — compute_session_mac with Suite1 vs Suite2 over the same (key, session_id, direction, seq, frame) must produce different MACs, otherwise an attacker who downgrades the suite negotiation could forge a Suite1 MAC for a Suite2 session. (2) session_id-binding — different MeshSessionId must produce different MACs, otherwise cross-session replay is possible. Add a small focused test file with 4-6 freshly-minted MAC comparisons. cc_2 domain (fcp-conformance + fcp-protocol).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T20:26:35.920969Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T20:27:52.576254Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T20:27:52.575790Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","protocol","tests"],"comments":[{"id":2994,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-the4k","author":"jemanuel","text":"e4eead4d adds session_mac_input_binding_conformance.rs with 8 tests pinning suite-binding (Suite1 HMAC-SHA256 vs Suite2 BLAKE3-keyed cross-verification rejection) and session_id-binding (cross-session replay rejection), plus a 4-way joint independence check and empty-frame edge case. All 8 pass locally in <0.01s via cargo test -p fcp-conformance --test session_mac_input_binding_conformance. Uses only public fcp_protocol::session API.","created_at":"2026-04-27T20:27:52Z"}]}
 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-thy","title":"fcp.twilio: SMS sending and receiving","description":"# fcp.twilio: SMS sending and receiving (FCP2)

## Goal
Provide core SMS/MMS capabilities:
- send outbound SMS (and MMS when enabled)
- read message status/history
- support inbound SMS via webhook-driven event flow (ingest handled in `flywheel_connectors-ugp`)

## Scope
### Outbound
- Send SMS to a single destination.
- Optional: bulk send with batching + rate limiting.
- Support idempotency keys to prevent duplicate sends.

### Status / history
- Get message details by SID.
- List messages with filters (date range, to/from).

### Media (MMS)
- List/download media attachments (bounded + host pinned).

## Capability model (illustrative)
- `twilio.sms.send`
- `twilio.sms.read`
- `twilio.sms.media.read`

Policy guidance:
- Outbound send is a real-world side effect; many orgs require approval for certain destinations.

## FCP2 requirements
- Single-zone binding.
- NetworkConstraints pinned to Twilio API host(s) and explicit media hosts.
- For sends:
  - receipts + audit events with message SID + to/from hashes (never raw phone numbers in logs)
  - strict log redaction for phone numbers and message bodies
- Taint model:
  - inbound message bodies are tainted by default

## Deliverables
- Operation schemas:
  - `twilio.sms.send`
  - `twilio.sms.get`
  - `twilio.sms.list`
  - `twilio.sms.media.list`
  - `twilio.sms.media.download`
- Idempotency strategy:
  - stable client idempotency key → dedupe cache/state

## Test strategy (MUST)
- Mock-only tests for:
  - send request formation
  - idempotency behavior
  - status polling
  - media download size limits
  - secret/PII redaction in logs

## Acceptance criteria
- Duplicate sends are mechanically prevented via idempotency.
- Logs and receipts never leak phone numbers or message bodies.
