 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-ti4ot","title":"conformance: hello replay window FIFO eviction + failed-verify non-poisoning tests","description":"session_nonce_replay_conformance.rs only covers happy-path duplicate detection. Add tests that lock in critical security invariants: (1) failed signature verification must NOT burn the replay-window nonce, otherwise a tampered hello could DoS a legitimate one; (2) timestamp-skew rejection must NOT burn the nonce; (3) attestation node-mismatch must NOT burn the nonce; (4) FIFO eviction allows re-acceptance after capacity overflow. All using public fcp_protocol::session API.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T18:53:58.888766Z","created_by":"jemanuel","updated_at":"2026-04-27T19:18:23.805052Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T19:18:23.804493Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["conformance","protocol","tests"],"comments":[{"id":2965,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-ti4ot","author":"jemanuel","text":"387b2162 adds 4 hello-replay conformance tests covering: (1) invalid-signature non-poisoning of replay window, (2) timestamp-skew non-poisoning, (3) attestation-node-mismatch non-poisoning, (4) FIFO eviction allows re-acceptance after capacity overflow. All 7 tests in session_nonce_replay_conformance.rs pass via rch (cargo test -p fcp-conformance --test session_nonce_replay_conformance).","created_at":"2026-04-27T19:18:23Z"}]}
